# Production readiness audit

Run this checklist against the **deployed site** (default: `https://skarpa.dev/`). If the user gives another URL (preview, localhost), use that instead.

**Do not guess.** Crawl the site with **Playwright MCP** (`browser_run_code_unsafe`, `browser_console_messages`).

## Discover routes (every run)

Build the crawl list at audit time. **Never use a hardcoded route list.**

1. Read `allRoutes` in `src/lib/data/site.ts` and collect each `href`.
2. Glob `src/routes/**/+page.svelte` and map each file to a path (`+page.svelte` → `/`, nested dirs → `/segment/...`).
3. Merge both lists, dedupe, sort. Flag any path present in one source but missing in the other (note in output; still crawl the union).
4. Optional cross-check: fetch live `/sitemap` and compare link hrefs to the merged list.

Use the merged list for all crawl, meta, and console checks.

## Steps (in order)

1. **Load every route** with `waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded'`. Record HTTP status, `document.title`, load time (ms), and whether `header`, `main`, and body text render after hydration.
2. **Console errors** — listen for `console` type `error` and `pageerror` on each route. A single route error is a fail for that check.
3. **Placeholder copy** — scan body text for `/lorem ipsum/i`, `/coming soon/i`, `/\\bTODO\\b/`, `/\\bFIXME\\b/`, `/your name here/i`.
4. **Links** — collect unique `a[href]` from `/`, `/sitemap`, and `/projects`. HTTP-check internal paths (prepend site origin). Skip `#`, `mailto:`, `tel:`. Relative `./` links are OK if they resolve in-browser. External social URLs may return bot blocks (LinkedIn 999, Facebook 400) in HEAD/GET; verify in browser before marking broken.
5. **Privacy** — confirm `/privacy` hydrates (not blank), content matches `src/lib/data/privacy.ts`, and footer links to it.
6. **Meta** — per route: `meta[name="description"]`, `link[rel="canonical"]`, favicon `link[rel="icon"]`. Flag canonical pointing at the wrong host (check `site.url` in `src/lib/data/site.ts` vs live domain).
7. **Mobile** — viewport `375×812`. Check `scrollWidth <= clientWidth + 2` on `/` plus at least three other discovered routes (prefer long pages listed under PageTOC in `design/ia/navigation.md`). Open the header sheet menu on `/` and confirm nav links appear.

## Output format

Reply with a **simple table only** (plus a one-line verdict). Use ✅ pass, ❌ fail, ⚠️ partial.

| Check | Status | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| **Content** | | |
| All placeholder text replaced with real info | | |
| No broken links (nav + project links) | | |
| Privacy page exists and is accurate | | |
| **Tech** | | |
| No console errors | | |
| Loads reasonably fast | | |
| Mobile responsive | | |
| **Meta** | | |
| Page title & description set (sharing/SEO) | | |
| Favicon works | | |

Then one line: **Production ready?** Yes / No / Almost — with blockers listed briefly.

## Pass thresholds

- **Loads reasonably fast:** each route under ~2 s on first load (note actual ms in Notes).
- **No console errors:** zero `pageerror` and zero console `error` across all routes.
- **Privacy accurate:** visible copy aligns with `privacy.ts`; mentions Vercel Analytics/Speed Insights when hosted on Vercel.
- **Meta:** every route has a unique `<title>`; description present after hydration; canonical matches live domain.

## Known project pitfalls

- **`EmphasisText`** keys segments as `segment.type + segment.value`. Duplicate `**word**` in one string causes `each_key_duplicate` and can blank the page (seen on `/privacy`).
- **`site.url`** must stay on `https://skarpa.dev/` (canonical domain). GitHub Pages fallback uses `BASE_PATH=/cv` but canonicals should still resolve to skarpa.dev.
- Favicons are inline SVG data URIs; do not fail because HTTP GET on `data:` returns 404.

## After the audit

- Report findings only unless the user asks to fix issues.
- If blockers are code bugs, cite the file and root cause briefly in Notes.
